item.description:
विश्वास-प्रस्तुतिः परिहृत&ndash;निखिल-नर-पति-वरण&ndash;
जनक-दुहितृ&ndash;कुच-तट-विहरण-समुचित&ndash;कर-तल !
मूलम् परिहृत&ndash;निखिल-नर-पति-वरण&ndash;
जनक-दुहितृ&ndash;कुच-तट-विहरण-समुचित&ndash;कर-तल !
शठकोपः (En) Here Swami Desikan salutes the unique valor that Sri RaAmachandra displayed at the Svayamvaram to win the hand and heart of Sita Piratti. Since none of the assembled kings other than Sri Raamachandra were able to string the Siva Dhanus, Sita Devi had to reject (happily) their wishes to marry her. O, Sri Raama! You bent and broke that mighty bow and qualified yourself to engage in amorous and conjugal sports with your bride.

विश्वास-प्रस्तुतिः अपार-पारावार-परिखा-परिवृत&ndash;
पर+++(→रावण)+++-पुर-परिसृत&ndash;दव-दहन&ndash;जवन&ndash;
पवन-भव&ndash;कपि-वर&ndash;परिष्वङ्ग-
भावित&ndash;सर्वस्व-दान !
मूलम् अपार-पारावार-परिखा-परिवृत&ndash;
पर+++(→रावण)+++-पुर-परिसृत&ndash;दव-दहन&ndash;जवन&ndash;
पवन-भव&ndash;कपि-वर&ndash;परिष्वङ्ग-
भावित&ndash;सर्वस्व-दान !
शठकोपः (En) Raama&rsquo;s power to bless one with every kind of Iswaryam including Moksham is covered by Swami Desikan here.
O Lord, who embraced HanumAn with joy over the good tidings of locating Sita&rsquo;s place of incarceration by the evil RAvaNA and for bringing back the KaNaiAzhi as Sita’s token of her love for Raama! Hail to Thee! Hail to Thee!
